{
  "local_port": 55998,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I make friends at new job?",
  "response": "Making friends at a new job can feel daunting, but it\u2019s a great opportunity to build meaningful relationships. Here are some practical tips to help you connect with your colleagues:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Be Approachable and Friendly**\n- **Smile and Greet People**: A warm smile and a simple \"hello\" or \"good morning\" can go a long way.\n- **Use Open Body Language**: Maintain eye contact, avoid crossing your arms, and be mindful of your posture.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Introduce Yourself**\n- **Take the Initiative**: Introduce yourself to your team and other colleagues. Share a bit about your background or role.\n- **Remember Names**: Use their name in conversation to show you\u2019re paying attention.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Ask Questions and Show Interest**\n- **Be Curious**: Ask about their roles, projects, or experiences at the company.\n- **Listen Actively**: Show genuine interest in what they\u2019re saying and respond thoughtfully.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Participate in Social Activities**\n- **Join Workplace Events**: Attend team lunches, coffee breaks, or after-work gatherings.\n- **Volunteer for Activities**: Participate in office events or committees to meet people outside your immediate team.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Offer Help and Collaborate**\n- **Be Supportive**: If a colleague seems overwhelmed, offer to help with their workload or share your expertise.\n- **Collaborate on Projects**: Working together is a great way to build rapport.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Find Common Interests**\n- **Talk About Hobbies**: Share your interests and ask about theirs (e.g., sports, TV shows, travel).\n- **Join Workplace Clubs**: If your workplace has clubs or groups (e.g., book clubs, fitness groups), join them.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Be Patient and Consistent**\n- **Give It Time**: Building friendships takes time, so don\u2019t rush it.\n- **Follow Up**: If you have a good conversation, follow up with them later to keep the connection alive.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Be Yourself**\n- **Authenticity Matters**: Don\u2019t try to be someone you\u2019re not. People appreciate genuine connections.\n- **Share Your Personality**: Let your unique qualities shine through in your interactions.\n\n---\n\nBy being proactive, friendly, and open, you\u2019ll naturally start forming connections. Remember, it\u2019s normal to feel a bit nervous, but most people are happy to welcome a new colleague!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
